msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:135
msgid ""
"`conn:run(...)` executes a remote command through the current SSH connection."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:137
msgid "The following call forms are supported:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:148
msgid "Argument rules:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:150
msgid "`conn:run(cmdline)`: `cmdline` is sent as the remote command string."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:151
msgid ""
"`conn:run(cmd, argsline)`: `cmd` is treated as the command, and `argsline` "
"is split using shell-style (`shlex`) rules."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:153
msgid ""
"`conn:run(cmd, args)`: `cmd` is a string and `args` is an array of strings. "
"Arguments are shell-quoted before remote execution."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:155
msgid "`conn:run(cmdline, options)`: `options` overrides this invocation."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:156
msgid "`conn:run(cmd, args, options)`: `options` overrides this invocation."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:157
msgid "`conn:run(options)`: `options` is a table."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:158
msgid ""
"When the second argument is a table: if it is an array "
"(consecutive integer keys `1..n`), it is treated as `args`; otherwise it is "
"treated as `options`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:161
msgid "When `conn:run(options)` is used, `options` currently supports:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:163
msgid "`cmd` (string, required): The command name or executable path."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:164
msgid "`args` (string[], optional): The argument list."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:165
msgid ""
"`cwd` (string, optional): Remote working directory. This is applied by "
"prepending `cd ... &&` to the generated remote shell command."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:167
msgid ""
"`env` (table, optional): Remote environment variables, where keys and values "
"are strings. This is applied by prepending `export ... &&` to the generated "
"remote shell command."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:170
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:170"
msgid "`stdin` (string, optional): String sent to the remote process stdin."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:171
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:171"
msgid ""
"`echo` (boolean, optional): Whether to echo the remote command before "
"execution. Defaults to `true`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:173
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:173"
msgid ""
"`check` (boolean, optional): Whether to raise an error immediately when the "
"exit status is not `0`. Defaults to `false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:175
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:175"
msgid ""
"`stdout` (string, optional): Stdout handling strategy. Supported values:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:175
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:175"
msgid "`\"inherit\"`: Inherit to the current terminal (default)."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:175
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:175"
msgid "`\"capture\"`: Capture into `res.stdout`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:175
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:175"
msgid "`\"null\"`: Discard the output."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:179
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:179"
msgid ""
"`stderr` (string, optional): Stderr handling strategy. Supported values:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:179
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.6.0/lua-api/ssh.md:179"
